<%- include('header'); -%>

<!-- Template for /help route -->

<p>
  This service allows to use external identities for <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Single_sign-on">single sign-on</a>. By using this service, you agree that the following data of authenticated identities is saved in our database and
  <strong>made available</strong> to selected applications (see below):
</p>

<ul>
  <li>name</li>
  <li>a unique personal identifier</li>
  <li>IDs, names, usernames, URIs, and access tokens (if applicable)</li>
</ul>

<p>
  Applications may further store and share the data by their own conditions.
  Passwords are <strong>never saved or shared in any way</strong>.
</p>

<p>
  After logging in, you will be able to see all data associated with your user account by clicking on the <a href="currentUser">My Data</a> link
  in the footer. You will also be able to delete your user account which results in the immediate removal of all your data
  from our database. <b>Note</b> that data used in associated applications will <b>not</b> be deleted when deleting your user account.
</p>

<% if (config.applications.length) { %>
<p>
  Applications with access to <%= config.title %>:
  <ul>
    <% config.applications.forEach(application => { %>
    <li>
      <a href="<%= application.url %>" target="_blank">
        <%= application.name %>
      </a>
    </li>
    <% }) %>
  </ul>
  On the <a href="<%= baseUrl %>sessions">sessions page</a>, you can assess your currently active sessions and which applications have initiated them.
</p>
<% } %>

<%- include('footer'); -%>
